sql:
SELECT station_name, total_turnstiles
FROM stations
ORDER BY total_turnstiles DESC;

SELECT station_name 
FROM stations 
ORDER BY station_name;

SELECT COUNT(turnstile_id) AS active_turnstiles
FROM station_turnstiles
WHERE station_id = 1 AND status = 'active';

external_knowledge:
- Top stations refer to the stations with the highest total weekend entries.; 
- Weekend entries refer to the number of entries recorded on weekends.; 
- Average entries per turnstile is calculated by dividing the total entries by the number of turnstiles.

